{"build_type":"library","description":"Toy per-thread bump allocator (de-globalization step 4 proof helper). Reads the thread-local cursor tls_cursor (FS+8), advances it by size, writes it back, returns the OLD cursor as the allocated address. Because tls_cursor is thread-local (FS-relative codegen), each thread bumps its OWN cursor with no shared state -> no race. This is the minimal shape of the real arena allocate, validated before migrating the real arena globals.","module_name":"bump-allocate-from-thread-local-arena","package_name":"bump-allocate-from-thread-local-arena","function_definitions":{"bump-allocate-from-thread-local-arena":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"size","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"global_read","dest":"cur","name":"tls_cursor"},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"newcur","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"alu_operation","operator":"+","target":"newcur","lhs":{"value":"cur"},"rhs":{"value":"size"}},{"instruction_type":"global_write","name":"tls_cursor","value":"newcur"},{"instruction_type":"return_statement","return_payload":{"value":"cur"}}]}}}